commit b44fe316526082b01b4b646af6b35133796fe312
Author: PhilippeKlein <philippe@birdbird.xyz>
Date:   Mon Jun 29 14:24:05 2026 +0100

    feat(filter): collision metafilter via Tab bang autocomplete + Esc clear (v0.5.14)
    
    Implements TASK-003 (FR10) on top of the TASK-001/002 dispatch infra.
    
    - actions: add AutocompleteBang (Tab / ctrl+i) to the Action union.
    - loop: map KEY_TAB and the "\t" byte (ctrl+i) to AutocompleteBang; the
      ghost-visibility gate lives in the reducer, not the input layer.
    - reducer: AutocompleteBang inserts a leading ! (cursor → 1) only when the
      "Tab to view collisions" ghost is visible (empty filter + at least one
      unresolved collision); no-op otherwise, so a second Tab never clears the !.
      The filter post-mutation sequence now clamps the selection onto a visible
      row (spec §3.4): engaging the metafilter from frame 1a moves the cursor to
      the first collision row; clearing to an empty result drops it to None.
    - renderer: metafilter-only prompt template for filter.raw == "!" — the literal
      ! followed by the dim "Type to filter" ghost with only T reverse-video
      (spec §6.5).
    - Esc clear (ClearFilter) already shipped in TASK-001; covered here by BDD.
    
    Tests: golden frame_2 (Tab autocomplete, rows 2/3, selection→2, !Type ghost,
    under-full frame ends at footer) and frame_esc_clear (byte-identical to the
    updated frame_1a); BDD collision_metafilter.feature (ghost-gated autocomplete,
    second-Tab and no-collision no-ops, ! as ordinary text, Esc clear); reducer and
    loop unit coverage. Readline matrix Tab/ctrl+i row reconciled 🔴 → ✅.
    
    226 passed under uv run pytest.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

